<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-06-08T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-06-08T14:00:00-05:00" n="363" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d363">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.51/1477a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-06-08T15:00:00-04:00">June 8,
                                    1939—3 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>106. Do you have any further indication as to intention of Brazilian
                            Government in regard to resumption payment on dollar bonds on July
                                1?<note n="18" xml:id="d363fn18">See paragraph numbered V in letter
                                from the Brazilian Minister for Foreign Affairs, March 8, <ref target="#pg_352">p. 352</ref>.</note> Time for possible
                            discussion is getting very short. Failure to afford opportunity for such
                            discussion will be regrettable.</p>
                        <p>Please report by cable.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>